## Vegetarian Yakisoba

# Ingredients
* 1 package fresh yakisoba noodles
* 2-3 leeks, white and light green part cut into thin circles and rinsed of dirt
* 4-8 inches of ginger, slices
* 8 baby bok choy, chopped
* 1/2 head napa cabbage, chopped
* 3 packages flat fried (aka aburaage) tofu, diced
* 1/2 cup Hoisin sauce such as Soy Vey brand, or teriyaki sauce containing garlic
* 1/4 cup miso paste
* cooking oil

# Optional: 
* 4 cloves of garlic, minced
* 2 1/2 tbsp black bean sauce added Lee Kum Kee Hoisin sauce
* 8-12 oz fresh mung bean sprouts, rinsed

# instructions
* 1. Heat oil in pan until it shimmers.
* 2. Fry ginger until fragrant. If using garlic, add and fry until fragrant.
* 3. Add leeks and fry until they are softened.
* 3. Add baby bok choy and napa cabbage. Stir fry until wilted.
* 4. Add Hoisin sauce and flat fried tofu. If using, add bean sprouts here are at very end. Stir until tofu warmed through.
* 5. Add noodle and stir fry until they are hot and cooked (they will start to stick a little).
